lar.  Ate a HT right off and that didn't make me feel too good, but the battle went pretty smoothly (if a bit hard on the mana).  Seems like it took 2 Siroccos and a Shock of Steel to take him down.  Pet survived at around 40% (with a heal or two).<br>
<br>
I hung around for a little while trying to get a feel for the spawn time and the pathing of the wanderer.  Looked around with a few eyes, ate a few rods, listened to the ooc chatter of the raiding party at the entrance...  Looks like about 17 or 18 minutes on the spawn time.  Once the Transient repopped I took him down again and then proceeded to try to pull the Dator right in the middle of the big &quot;clearing,&quot; but unfortunately Mr. Wanderer was a bit too close and he aggroed.  Rather than risk losing level 57 I chose to gate back to TD and give it another go tomorrow.<br>
<br>
From what I've seen, assuming the Dators aren't any harder than the Transients, this looks like it'll be a hell of a great spot at 57 once I get the pulling strategy down.  No epic required.  That wanderer (or perhaps Wanderer<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> s</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, I didn't really notice if it was always the same mob) is the only problem I see...  gonna have to find a way to reliably take care of him.  Heh, probably not that big of a deal but I just hate mobs that refuse to stand in one place and wait to be killed.  They always seem to provide a monkey wrench at just the right time to derail my well-oiled exp-gaining machinery. <br>
<br>
At any rate...  the way I see it, the respawn time is about the same as Brownies but the mobs are a couple levels higher, there's a ZEM (I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> assume</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->) and I can probably kill 3 or <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> maybe</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> 4 in one cycle, as opposed to 2.  So right away this is probably 2x better than Brownies (that's the benchmark I use to compare all of my endeavors these days <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).  Of course Brownies are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> safe</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, so there is that to take into consideration <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Gonna see if a Shammy friend of mine (55) wants to tag along tomorrow...  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> seems</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> like we'd clean up <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR><CENTER><hr size=1 WIDTH=75%>
