<br>
Centi Dators were the test mob. <br>
<br>
Pulled with Malise:  Nuke as mob nears fear mode.  Used Bo3 and damage shield on pet, and self only buffs and items.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Earth pet info:<br>
first pet can usually tank mob to about 40% second pet can finish.<br>
Pros:  Earth roots keep them from running, also allows some safty when chain casting if your late with second pet.<br>
Cons: Root Makes pet Take extra damage when mob would normally be in fear mode. <br>
<br>
Could handle up to a double pull with earth rooting.  When the first pet drops only one mob can run after you so depending on root time your in single mob fight mode,  Just run back and forth if a mob gets on you and it will trun on pet, repeat till all dead. <br>
<br>
Earth Pet fully dressed in all possible summoned gear.  This pet could end fight with about 20% life when you nuke 2 times for say 2k and heal pet once.   After fight heal a couple times and med if needed and your good for next pull,  Down time varies on buffs.  Thats only 1 extr nuke and a heal from chain pet tactic.  because pet tanks longer there is more med time and regen time so i mod a lot and usually regen effectively during combat. <br>
<br>
Note: forgot to use muzzle on earth pet. <br>
<br>
Air pet info:  Newer buffed air pet after 8/15/patch<br>
Dressed and air pet with all posible summoned gear, remebered muzzel.<br>
This pet by far was better than earth,  A single heal and Nuke you could med the whole fight.  Air was very easy to heal up.  I even played around with tanking a bit to give pet back combat arch.  <br>
Pros: Was better than earth in effectiveness.  When mob turns to run Air gets rear attacks.<br>
Cons:  If you have to chain cast you dont have room for error. <br>
<br>
MS3 Pet:<br>
Sucked.<br>
Pros:  One of them had a nice damage shield.  Pet worm scared the crap out of a few people. <br>
Cons: Seemed to vary in lvl?  some pets died easier than others.  No root to make sloppy chain casting safe.  <br>
<br>
I'll try Fire and Water next time and an undressed air pet to get a comparisson. <br>
<br>
<br>
